{"title_page": "Andrew Baird (footballer)", "text_new": "{{for|the Scottish footballer, born 1979|Andy Baird}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2019}}\n{{Use British English|date=April 2017}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Andrew Baird\n| fullname = Andrew Baird<ref name=\"QPFC\" />\n| birth_date = {{Birth date|1866|6|11}}\n| birth_place = [[Irvine, North Ayrshire|Irvine]], Scotland\n| death_date = {{Death year and age|1916|1866}}<ref name=\"Litster\" />\n| death_place = \n| height = \n| position = [[Goalkeeper (association football)|Goalkeeper]]\n| years1 = 1888\u20131889\n| clubs1 = Kilbirnie\n| caps1 = \n| goals1 = \n| years2 = 1889\u20131890\n| clubs2 = Irvine\n| caps2 = \n| goals2 = \n| years3 = 1890\u20131894\n| clubs3 = [[Queen's Park F.C.|Queen's Park]]\n| caps3 = 0\n| goals3 = 0\n| nationalyears1 = 1892\u20131894\n| nationalteam1 = [[Scotland national football team|Scotland]]\n| nationalcaps1 = 2\n| nationalgoals1 = 0\n}}\n'''Andrew Baird''' (11 June 1866 \u2013 1916) was a Scottish amateur [[association football|football]] [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] who played for [[Queen's Park F.C.|Queen's Park]].<ref name=\"QPFC\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.qpfc.com/appearances/b/bairda.htm |title=QPFC.com \u2013 A Historical Queen's Park FC Website |website=www.qpfc.com |accessdate=25 July 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"Litster\">{{Cite book |title=Record of Pre-War Scottish League Players |last=Litster |first=John |publisher=PM Publications |location=Norwich}}</ref> He was capped by [[Scotland national football team|Scotland]] at international level.<ref>{{Cite book |title=Scotland's Who's Who: One Hundred and Forty Years of Scottish International Footballers 1872\u20132013 |last=Smith |first=Paul |date=30 September 2013 |publisher=Pitch Publishing Ltd |isbn=9781909178847 |location=Durrington |page=18 |language=English}}</ref>\n\n== Honours ==\n'''Queen's Park'''\n\n* [[Scottish Cup]]: [[1892\u201393 Scottish Cup|1892\u201393]]<ref>{{Soccerbase seas