| image              = \n| caption            = \n| native_name        = {{linktext|\u674e\u73b0}}\n| native_name_lang   = zh\n| pronunciation      = L\u01d0 Xi\u00e0n\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1991|10|19}}\n| birth_place        = [[Xianning]], [[Hubei]]\n| nationality        = Chinese\n| alma_mater         = [[Beijing Film Academy]]\n| occupation         = Actor\n| years_active       = 2011\u2013present\n| agent              = Easy Entertainment\n| module             = {{Infobox Chinese|child=yes|order=st\n| t= \u674e\u73fe | s= {{linktext|\u674e|\u73b0}} \n  | p = L\u01d0 Xi\u00e0n\n}}\n}}\n'''Li Xian''' ({{zh|s=\u674e\u73b0}}; born 19 October 1991)<ref name=\"The Beijing News\">{{cite news |last1=Liu |first1=Wei |title=Li Xian really wants to buy a cup of coffee |url=http://epaper.bjnews.com.cn/html/2019-12/17/content_774177.htm?div=-1 |accessdate=1 April 2020 |work=[[The Beijing News]] |publisher=The Beijing News |archiveurl=http://epaper.bjnews.com.cn/html/2019-12/17/content_774177.htm?div=-1/|archivedate=April 2, 2020|date=December 17, 2019 |pages=C04 |language=zh}}</ref> is a [[Mainland China]] actor. Made his feature film debut in 2011, and best known for his roles in the drama ''[[Go Go Squid!]]''.<ref name=xian>{{cite web |last1=Yau |first1=Elaine |title=Who is Li Xian, rising star of China TV hit Go Go Squid? |url=https://www.scmp.com/lifestyle/entertainment/article/3021194/who-li-xian-rising-star-chinas-go-go-squid-hit-television |website=South China Morning Post |accessdate=1 April 2020|archiveurl=https://www.scmp.com/lifestyle/entertainment/article/3021194/who-li-xian-rising-star-chinas-go-go-squid-hit-television|archivedate=August 5, 2019 |language=en |date=August 4, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nLi Xian was born as Li Han ({{zh|s=\u674e\u73fe}}) on 19 October 1991 in [[Xianning]] City, and grew up in [[Jingzhou]] City, [[Hubei]] Province.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ent.sina.com.cn/ku/star_info_index.d.html?id=fyhvyie0226195|title=Li Xian Profile|website=Sina|language=zh}}</ref>  He studied at Jingzhou Middle School one of the best school in the City. In 2009 he thought to studying STEM subjects in college, but after failing the annual college entrance examination, he took the test again and enter the 2010 Department of [[Beijing Film Academy]] Performance Department.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.ifeng.com/a/20160402/48317189_0.shtml||title=Jingzhou chubby turned into a half-cooked male god|script-title=zh:\u56fe\u6587\uff1a\u8346\u5dde\u5c0f\u80d6\u53d8\u8eab\u534a\u719f\u7537\u795e|website=ifeng|publisher=Chutian Metropolis Daily|date=April 2, 2016|language=zh}}</ref> For the convenience of entry, Li changed his name \"{{zh|s=\u665b}}\" into Xian \"{{zh|s=\u73b0}}\" which is mean \"present\".<ref name=\"The Beijing News\"/>  And he was also the first college student to be admitted to the academy in Jingzhou, Hubei Province.\n\n==Career==\n===2011\u20132018: Acting debut and Rising popularity===\nIn 2011, Li made his debut in the director Wang Jing's film, \"A Thousand Arrows Through Heart\" iIn which he played Li Baoli's son Xiaobao, a boy who is full of resentment towards his mother and has a restrained voice because of his father's early death. He got his first role in [[Feng Shui (2012 film)|''Feng Shui'']] when he was a sophomore at the academy. He got the role due to his age and the fact that the director, who was affiliated with the academy, was looking for someone from Hubei province, where Li was from.''<ref name=\"feng\">{{cite web|url=http://www.jznews.com.cn/comnews/system/2013/02/22/010784530.shtml|date=February 22, 2013|website=JZ News|language=zh|script-title=zh:\u300a\u4e07\u7bad\u7a7f\u5fc3\u300b\"\u5c0f\u5b9d\" \u6625\u8282\u56de\u8346\u5dde\u62dc\u5e74}}</ref>'' In 2013, he starred in the romance teen flick ''Singing When We Are Young'', produced by [[Andy Lau]].<ref name=sing>{{cite web|url=http://www.rbc.cn/bobo/2013-07/31/cms29689article.shtml|script-title=zh:\u4e13\u8bbf\u300a\u521d\u604b\u672a\u6ee1\u300b\u5bfc\u6f14\u674e\u5a1f\u3001\u6f14\u5458\u674e\u73b0|date=July 31, 2013|publisher=Radio Beijing Corporation |language=zh-cn}}</ref> \n\nIn 2014, Li made his small-screen debut in the omnibus web drama''City Of Fantasy''.<ref name=city>{{cite web|url=http://ent.163.com/14/1029/12/A9NLMTKS000333J5.html|script-title=zh:\u674e\u73b0\u300a\u5947\u5999\u4e16\u7eaa\u300b\u732e\u8367\u5e55\u521d\u543b \u6f14\u6280\u5927\u53d7\u597d\u8bc4|date=October 29, 2014|website=Netease|language=zh}}</ref>\nIn 2015, he co-starred with Chen Xiao, Du Tianhao and Liu Ruilin in the youth campus network drama \" Brothers Sleeping on My Upper Bunk \", and played the role of \"Loyal and Mighty Boy\" Xie Xun, a member of the 330 dormitory of Hudu University. In December, he starred in the music video of [[Zhang Jiao]]'s \" I'm Jiang Xiaobai 2016 \" and also starred in the second edition MV of [[Luhan]]\u2019s Medal .\n\nIn 2015, Li starred in the coming-of-age brotherhood web series ''[[Who Sleeps My Bro]]''.<ref name=sleep1>{{cite web|url=http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/micro-reading/2016-03/28/content_24142835.htm|script-title=zh:\u300a\u7761\u5728\u6211\u4e0a\u94fa\u7684\u5144\u5f1f\u300b\u674e\u73b0\u51fa\u90535\u5e74\u5e05\u6c14\u8d70\u7ea2|date=March 28, 2016|website=China Daily|language=zh}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://ent.ifeng.com/a/20160201/42571343_0.shtml|script-title=zh:\u300a\u7761\u5728\u6211\u4e0a\u94fa\u7684\u5144\u5f1f\u300b\u6b63\u80fd\u91cf\u9752\u6625\u5267\u4e00\u6837\u662f|website=ifeng|date=February 1, 2016|language=zh}}</ref> The series was later adapted into a film starring the original cast. In the same year he participated in the Shanghai International Film Festival Red Carpet.<ref name=sleep>{{cite web|url=http://ent.ifeng.com/a/20151216/42545751_0.shtml|script-title=zh:\u300a\u7761\u5728\u6211\u4e0a\u94fa\u7684\u5144\u5f1f\u300b\u5b9a\u68634\u67081\u65e5 \u70ed\u8840\u9752\u6625\u71c3\u503c\u7206\u8868|website=ifeng|date=December 16, 2015|language=zh}}</ref> In the same year Li co-starred alongside [[Zhang Ruoyun]] and [[Jiao Junyan]] in the crime medical web drama ''[[Medical Examiner Dr. Qin]]'' as the criminal police captain Lin Tao,<ref name=qin>{{cite web|url=http://ent.163.com/16/1018/12/C3LMKDV3000380EO.html|script-title=zh:\u300a\u6cd5\u533b\u79e6\u660e\u300b\u83b7\u8d5e\u4e0b\u996d\u5267 \u674e\u73b0\"\u4e09\u526f\u8138\u5b54\"\u53cd\u5dee\u840c_\u7f51\u6613\u5a31\u4e50|website=Netease|date=October 18, 2016|language=zh}}</ref> which was acclaimed for both its storyline and performance.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bjnews.com.cn/ent/2016/11/25/424878.html|script-title=zh:\u6f14\u5458\u65b0\u52bf\u529b\u4e28\u674e\u73b0\uff1a\u521a\u62cd\u300a\u6cd5\u533b\u79e6\u660e\u300b\uff0c\u8fd8\u633a\"\u5012\u80c3\u53e3\"\u7684|date=November 25, 2016|website=Beijing News|language=zh}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/culture/2016-12/14/content_27663593.htm|title=Behind the success of 'Medical Examiner Dr. Qin'|work=China Daily|date=December 14, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.globaltimes.cn/content/1023044.shtml|title=Sohu TV drama \u2018Medical Examiner Dr. Qin\u2019 receives more than 1.2 billion views|work=Global Times|date=December 11, 2016}}</ref>\n\nIn 2016, he co-starred with [[Angelababy]], [[Jing Bairan]], and [[Bai Yu]] in the romatic movie \"[[Love O2O (film)|Love O2O]]\", and played the roommate of the leading actor Xiao Nai, Yu Banshan in the film. In 2017, his web drama ''[[Tientsin Mystic]]'' which was broadcast internationally on [[Netflix]].<ref name=tien>{{cite web|url=https://news.china.com/news100/11038989/20170706/30927237.html|script-title=zh:\u300a\u6cb3\u795e\u300b\u5b9a\u6863719 \"\u987d\u75de\u6cb3\u795e\"\u674e\u73b0\u8d64\u8eab\u79c0\u6c34\u6027|date=July 6, 2017|website=China.com|language=zh}}</ref> made him received a lot of praise for \"acting burst\", and also accumulated his first fans for him. The job offer he received was one year in a row, and in order to enter the role attentively, he refused other jobs during the filming.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/a/201804/18/WS5ad68c6aa3105cdcf6518e5c.html|title=Dramatic improvement |website=China Daily|date=April 18, 2018}}</ref> and <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thepaper.cn/newsDetail_forward_1763753|script-title=zh:\u4e13\u8bbf\uff5c\u674e\u73b0\uff1a\u4e0d\u662f\u6211\u591a\u5e05\uff0c\u662f\u90ed\u5f97\u53cb\u5f88\u5e05|date=August 17, 2017|website=The Paper|language=zh}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://ent.people.com.cn/n1/2017/0913/c86955-29532241.html|script-title=zh:\u300a\u6cb3\u795e\u300b\u674e\u73b0\uff1a\u6f14\u597d\u6bcf\u4e2a\u89d2\u8272 \u4f53\u4f1a\u4e0d\u4e00\u6837\u7684\u4eba\u751f|date=September 13, 2017|website=People's Daily|language=zh}}</ref> \n\nIn 2018, Li starred in the romance drama  ''[[Only Side by Side with You]]'' as a special forces agent.<ref name=side>{{cite web|url=http://ent.sina.com.cn/v/m/2017-04-07/doc-ifyecezv2449403.shtml|script-title=zh:\u300a\u5357\u65b9\u6709\u4e54\u6728\u300b\u66dd\u9635\u5bb9 \u9648\u4f1f\u9706\u674e\u73b0\u4e0a\u6f14\u5236\u670d\u8bf1\u60d1|website=Sina|language=zh|date=April 7, 2017}}</ref> He starred in Australia's ''Explore Melbourne'' China campaign,<ref>{{cite web |last1=Staff |first1=The |title=Australia Launches 'Explore Melbourne' Campaign Aimed at Chinese Tourists |url=https://brandinginasia.com/australia-launches-explore-melbourne-campaign-aimed-chinese-tourists/ |website=Branding in Asia Magazine |accessdate=2 April 2020 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180314055947/https://brandinginasia.com/australia-launches-explore-melbourne-campaign-aimed-chinese-tourists/ |archivedate=March 14, 2018 |language=en |date=March 14, 2018}}</ref> as well as the Visit Victoria TV's commercial<ref>{{cite news |last1=Sun |first1=Herald |title=Visit Victoria wants to attract wealthy Chinese Millennials |url=https://www.heraldsun.com.au/news/victoria/visit-victoria-wants-to-attract-wealthy-chinese-millennials/news-story/918e8a2da3ae9e646959748e172b71dc |accessdate=2 April 2020 |work=[[Herald Sun]] |date=March 12, 2018 |quote=Actor Li Xian will front a Visit Victoria TV commercial aimed at enticing wealthy young Chinese Millennials to come to Melbourne}}</ref>\n\n===2019\u2013present: Breakthrough===\nIn 2019, Li starred in the romance comedy drama Go Go Squid! as a brooding esports champion, marked a breakthrough for him. Gained 20 million followers in 2019, as well as endorsement and awards<ref name=xian></ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Canaves |first1=Sky |title=CBI Case Study: Male Celebrities Give Beauty Marketing a Makeover |url=http://chinafilminsider.com/case-study-male-celebrities-beauty/ |website=China Film Insider |accessdate=1 April 2020 |language=en |date=15 October 2019 |quote=Li Xian\u2019s performance as a brooding esports champion on \u201cGo Go Squid!\u201d marked a breakthrough for the actor.}}</ref><ref name=squid>{{cite web|url=http://ent.163.com/18/0214/11/DAJQFEU5000380EN.html|script-title=zh:\u300a\u871c\u6c41\u7096\u9c7f\u9c7c\u300b\u6768\u7d2b\u674e\u73b0\u840c\u59b9\u9047\u7537\u795e\u4e00\u89c1\u949f\u60c5|date=February 14, 2018|website=Netease|language=zh}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://ent.huanqiu.com/movie/yingshi-neidi/2019-07/15095685.html?agt=15422|script-title=zh:\u300a\u4eb2\u7231\u7684\uff0c\u70ed\u7231\u7684\u300b\u5b9a\u68630709 \u6768\u7d2b\u674e\u73b0\u5f00\u542f\u70ed\u8840\u751c\u7231|date=July 5, 2019|website=Global Times|language=zh}}</ref> The same year, he starred in the wuxia drama ''[[Sword Dynasty]]'' produced by [[Feng Xiaogang]]. \n\nIn 2020, Li appeared in [[CCTV New Year's Gala]] for the first time, performing the song item \"Hello 2020\".<ref>{{cite web |last1=CGTN |title=2020 Spring Festival Gala unveils programs |url=https://news.cgtn.com/news/2020-01-23/2020-Spring-Festival-Gala-unveils-programs-NuxacNCF0Y/index.html |website=news.cgtn.com |publisher=CGTN |accessd