on, England |isbn = 0-333-34776-5 |oclc = 16604744 |ref = harv}}\n* {{cite book |last=Kowalsky |first=Daniel |title= Stalin and the Spanish Civil War |location = New York, NY |publisher = Columbia University Press |year = 2008 |ref = harv}}\n* {{cite book |editor1-last = Luke\u0161 |editor1-first = Igor |editor2-first=Erik |editor2-last=Goldstein |year=1999 |title = The Munich Crisis, 1938: Prelude to World War II |url = https://archive.org/details/munichcrisis193800igor |url-access = registration |location = London, England; Portland, Oregon |publisher = Frank Cass |isbn = 978-0-7146-8056-9}}\n* {{cite news |first=Jorge |last=Majfud |author-link = Jorge Majfud |url = http://thehumanist.com/magazine/july-august-2016/features/rescuing-memory |publisher = The Humanist |year=2016 |title= Rescuing Memory: the Humanist Interview with Noam Chomsky |ref = harv}}\n* {{cite book |last=Mittermaier |first = Ute Anne |year=2010 |chapter=Charles Donnelly, 'Dark Star' of Irish Poetry and Reluctant Hero of the Irish Left |editor-last1=Clark |editor-first1=David|editor-last2=\u00c1lavez |editor-first2=Rub\u00e9n Jarazo |title='To Banish Ghost and Goblin': New Essays on Irish Culture |location = Oleiros (La Coru\u00f1a) |publisher= Netbiblo |pages=191\u2013200 |isbn = 978-0-521-73780-7 |ref = harv}}\n* {{cite book |last=Neulen |first=Hans Werner |title = In the skies of Europe \u2013 Air Forces allied to the Luftwaffe 1939\u20131945 |year=2000 |publisher= The Crowood Press |location = Ramsbury, Marlborough, England |isbn = 1-86126-799-1 |ref = harv}}\n* {{cite book |last=Orwell |first=George |author-link = George Orwell |year=2000 |orig-year = 1938 |title = Homage to Catalonia |publisher=Penguin, Martin Secker & Warburg |location=Londo, England n |isbn=0-14-118305-5 |oclc = 42954349 |ref = harv}}\n* {{cite book |last= Othen |first=Christopher |year=2008 |title = Franco's International Brigades: Foreign Volunteers and Fascist Dictators in the Spanish Civil War |publisher=Reportage Press |location = London, England |ref = harv}}\n* {{cite book |last= Payne |first= Stanley G. |url= http://www.cambridge.org/us/academic/subjects/history/twentieth-century-european-history/spanish-civil-war |title=The Spanish Civil War |year=2012 |isbn = 978-0-521-17470-1 | publisher = Cambridge University Press |ref = harv}}\n* {{Cite book |last = Payne |first = Stanley G. |year = 2004 |title = The Spanish Civil War, the Soviet Union, and Communism |publisher = Yale University Press |location = New Haven, CT; London, England |isbn = 0-300-10068-X |oclc = 186010979 |ref = harv}}\n* {{cite book |last = Payne |first = Stanley G. |chapter-url = http://libro.uca.edu/payne2/payne26.htm |chapter=The Spanish Civil War of 1936-1939 |title = A History of Spain and Portugal |volume = 2 |publisher= University of Wisconsin Press |year=1973 |via = Library of Iberian resources online |access-date = 15 May 2007 |ref = harv}}\n* {{cite book |last = Payne |first = Stanley G. |url = https://books.google.com/books?id=NiD3UeOCSGsC&pg=PA200 |title = Fascism in Spain, 1923\u20131977 |year = 1999 |publisher = University of Wisconsin Press |isbn = 0-299-16564-7 |ref = harv}}\n* {{cite book |last = Payne |first = Stanley G. |url = https://books.google.com/books?id=KPgPFqXub14C |title = Franco and Hitler: Spain, Germany, and World War II |year = 2008 |location = [[New Haven, Connecticut|Connecticut]], [[Connecticut|CT]] |isbn = 978-0-300-12282-4 |publisher =Yale University Press |ref = harv}}\n* {{cite book |last=Preston |first=Paul |author-link=Paul Preston |year=1978 |title= The Coming of the Spanish Civil War |publisher=Macmillan |location=London |isbn=0-333-23724-2 |oclc= 185713276 |ref = harv}}\n* {{cite book |last=Preston |first=Paul |orig-year=1986 |year = 1996 |title = A Concise history of the Spanish Civil War |publisher = Fontana |location=London |isbn = 978-0-00-686373-1 |oclc = 231702516 |ref = harv}}\n* {{cite book |last=Preston |first=Paul |year=2006 |title=The Spanish Civil War: Reaction, Revolution, and Revenge |publisher=WW Norton & Co. |location = New York, NY |isbn=0-393-32987-9 |url = https://archive.org/details/spanishcivilwarr00pres |ref = harv}}\n* {{cite book |last1 = Radosh |first1 = Ronald |author1-link= Ronald Radosh |last2 = Habeck |first2 = Mary |last3 = Sevostianov |first3 = Grigory |year = 2001 |title = Spain betrayed: the Soviet Union in the Spanish Civil War |publisher=Yale University Press |location = New Haven, CT; London, England |isbn = 0-300-08981-3 |oclc = 186413320 |ref = harv}}\n* {{cite book |last = Richardson |first = R. Dan |year=2015 |orig-year = 1982 |title = Comintern Army: The International Brigades and the Spanish Civil War |publisher = University Press of Kentucky |location=Lexington, Kentucky |isbn=978-0-8131-6437-3 |ref = harv}}\n* {{cite book |last = O'Riordan |first = Michael |authorlink= Michael O'Riordan |year= 2005 |title= The Connolly Column |publisher = Warren & Pell |location = Pontypool, Wales |ref = harv}}\n* {{cite book |last = Rust |first = William |author-link = William Rust (journalist) |year=2003 |type = reprint |orig-year = 1939 |title = Britons in Spain: A History of the British Battalion of the XV International Brigade |publisher = Warren & Pell |location = [[Pontypool, Wales]] |ref = harv}}\n* {{cite book |last1 = Santos |first1 = Juli\u00e1 |last2=Casanova |first2 = Juli\u00e1n |author2-link = Juli\u00e1n Casanova Ruiz |last3 = Sol\u00e9 I Sabat\u00e9 |first3 = Josep Maria |last4 = Villarroya |first4 = Joan |last5= Moreno |first5 = Francisco |title = Victimas de la guerra civil |publisher = Temas de Hoy |year= 1999 |location= Madrid |language = es |ref = harv}}\n* {{cite book |title = The Victorious Counter-revolution: The Nationalist Effort in the Spanish Civil War |url = https://books.google.com/books?id=jSO-dC5ac_EC&pg=PA205 |first=Michael |last=Seidman |publisher = University of Wisconsin Press |year=2011 |isbn = 978-0-299-24964-9}}\n* {{cite book |last= Stoff |first = Laurie |t